                "description": {
                    "chat": "",
                    "unidentified": "",
                    "value": "<p>The frost worm emits a hypnotic trill. Each non-frost worm creature within 100 feet must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"will\" data-pf2-dc=\"32\" data-pf2-traits=\"auditory,concentrate,enchantment,mental,primal\" data-pf2-label=\"Worm Trill DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Will</span> save. The effects of Worm Trill last for 1 round, but if the frost worm uses this ability again on subsequent rounds, it extends this duration by 1 round for any creature already affected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and is immune to Worm Trill for 24 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Fascinated]{Fascinated} by the frost worm.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the fascinated condition doesn't end if the frost worm uses hostile actions against the creature.</p>"
